This paper deals with a variant of bin packing, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a lower bound, which involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, and hence could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) or information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves a combination of heuristics and analysis, which could be categorized under computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents results based on a computer search, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
